2 Garlic
1 packet Jasmine rice
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
1 packet Japanese Dressing
1 Cucumber
1 packet Prawn & Chive Wontons
1 packet Sriracha
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
20 g plant-based butter
1 drizzle olive oil
1 tsp sesame oil
1.25 cup water (for the rice)

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the plant-based butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and a generous pinch of salt to pan and bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and all the water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber into rounds.

• When the rice has 10 minutes remaining, in a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook prawn wontons until starting to brown, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water (watch out, it may spatter!), then cover with foil or a lid.
• Cook until the water has evaporated and wontons are tender and heated through, 4-5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, cucumber, plant-based mayo, sriracha and the sesame oil in a large bowl.
• Toss to combine and season to taste.
• Divide garlic rice between bowls. Top with prawn & chive wontons and cucumber
slaw.
• Garnish with crispy shallots. Drizzle over Japanese dressing to serve. Enjoy!